---
<article class="border-l-4 border-[hsl(24,95%,53%)] pl-6">
  <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-1">July 12, 2026</h2>
  <p class="text-sm text-gray-500 mb-4">
    Follow-up to the same-day core meta-description pass. Tightened the <code>meta description</code> on the
    <strong>53 programmatic geo pages</strong> that ran 161&ndash;227 characters and truncated in search results.
    Each rewrite keeps the location and its most distinctive one or two specialties (the local-SEO value),
    leads with the primary keyword, and closes on a soft CTA within 155 characters. No location-specific
    keywords were dropped wholesale, only trimmed to the strongest few per market.
  </p>

  <p class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-700 mb-1">Pages tightened (53)</p>
  <ul class="text-sm text-gray-600 mb-4 list-disc pl-5 space-y-1">
    <li><a href="/services/farriers" class="text-[hsl(24,95%,53%)] hover:underline">Farriers</a>: 17 state pages (Arizona, California, Texas, Florida, and more)</li>
    <li><a href="/services/equine-boarding" class="text-[hsl(24,95%,53%)] hover:underline">Equine boarding</a>: 10 metro pages (Lexington, Ocala, Wellington, Scottsdale, and more)</li>
    <li><a href="/services/dog-training" class="text-[hsl(24,95%,53%)] hover:underline">Dog training</a>: 10 metro pages (Austin, Chicago, Denver, Nashville, and more)</li>
    <li><a href="/services/livestock-services" class="text-[hsl(24,95%,53%)] hover:underline">Livestock services</a>: 10 state pages (Texas, Kansas, Nebraska, Montana, and more)</li>
    <li><a href="/find-breeders" class="text-[hsl(24,95%,53%)] hover:underline">Find breeders</a>: 5 species pages (dogs, horses, goats, sheep, cattle)</li>
    <li><a href="/dog-parks" class="text-[hsl(24,95%,53%)] hover:underline">Dog parks</a>: the dynamic per-city template (all city pages)</li>
  </ul>

  <p class="text-sm text-gray-500">
    SEO only: no on-page copy, routing, or navigation changed. The dog-parks change was made at the template
    literal so it applies to every generated city page while preserving the interpolated city name. With this
    pass, every audited page's meta description now sits within the search-result character budget.
  </p>
</article>
